For this purpose, the P-Cys-modified gold electrode was placed in the cell containing GQDs and subsequently, electrochemical deposition of GQDs on the electrode surface was conducted through CV with 15 consecutive cycles in the potential range of 0–1V vs. Ag/AgCl (Fig. 2
                        ). l-Cys has one NH2 groups and that can easily be oxidized to produce NH· Covalent bond (CN) is then formed by the free radical reaction of NH⋯CO group of GQDs with excellent stability. Therefore, the covalent bond (OCNH) might be formed between carbonyl group of GQDs and the amino group of P-Cys. It is important to point out that during the high potential scan rate, the amino free radical will easily form and the polymerization of the poly amino acid film could be formed on the surface of the GQDs. Therefore, P-Cys-GQDs was prepared in this step. It is known that the electron withdrawing oxygen-containing groups on P-Cys are beneficial to the combination with carbon based materials from the electrostatic point of view. Therefore, the GQDs can be interact with PCys via and −NH3
                        + side groups, which allow forming distinctive self-assembly network between the GQDs. Finally, thin film of P-Cys-GQDs was obtained at the surface of Au electrode.
